    vs expected 42, delta 5).
  - Medium: RAG dominates (+46.7%). This is the ambiguous method-name
    category where Grep struggles most (save, delete, findOne across
    modules). RAG's semantic search finds the right file/method more
    reliably.
  - Hard: Tie at 50%. Both agents handle inner classes/enums but
    struggle with overloaded methods in the same class.
  - Edge: Grep slightly ahead. RAG loses on annotation types (@interface)
    where embedding semantics differ from exact text matching.

